Hi everyone,

We at Team 7415 just released a template for our swerve code that we have been using for the past two seasons. It’s nothing special and not fancy at all but it is really simple and has features like PathPlanner, Odometry, and more built in. Also, the forked swerve library lets you use a Canivore on the drivetrain motors. It’s really customizable and very good to help teams get off of their feet with swerve.

Here is the link:

GitHub

GitHub - Jaguar-Robotics/FRC7415-SwerveTemplate

Contribute to Jaguar-Robotics/FRC7415-SwerveTemplate development by creating an account on GitHub.

If you have any issues or questions, please let me know. Good luck to all teams competing at champs!
